75
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:43,509
(explosion, clattering, men shouting)

76
00:03:43,533 --> 00:03:44,699
I mean, you really,

77
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,665
you just could not leave them unattended.

78
00:03:46,765 --> 00:03:48,199
(explosion)

79
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:51,566
We just kind of had to
swallow your own fear.

80
00:03:53,099 --> 00:03:55,900
NARRATOR: A triage officer
made the grim decisions

81
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,066
as to who might be saved

82
00:03:58,165 --> 00:04:01,566
and those for whom there was no hope.

83
00:04:01,665 --> 00:04:04,633
FUREY: One of the things that
initially was so difficult

84
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:07,566
was what we called "expected" patients.

85
00:04:07,665 --> 00:04:10,266
And these were patients
that would be brought in

86
00:04:10,365 --> 00:04:12,800
from the battlefield and it was determined

87
00:04:12,899 --> 00:04:15,500
they had no chance to survive.

88
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,199
But they weren't dead yet.

89
00:04:19,332 --> 00:04:20,665
They brought in a...

90
00:04:20,766 --> 00:04:24,065
a young soldier who had a head injury,

91
00:04:24,165 --> 00:04:27,632
and they said, "He's expected."

92
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:30,000
I kind of freaked out, uh,

93
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:33,165
and I decided that, no, they were wrong,

94
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:36,332
and I was gonna take care of this patient.

95
00:04:36,432 --> 00:04:38,932
I told the corpsman to get me blood.

96
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:40,699
And he's saying, "Well, Lieutenant,

97
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,566
the patient is expected."

98
00:04:42,665 --> 00:04:44,566
I said, "Get me blood."

99
00:04:44,665 --> 00:04:47,600
So, I take off the dressing, and...

100
00:04:47,699 --> 00:04:51,233
the whole back of his head had been gone.

101
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:52,865
When that happened,

102
00:04:52,966 --> 00:04:56,266
all the blood I had been
giving him came out.

103
00:04:56,365 --> 00:05:00,632
A friend of mine who came over
just walked me out of there.

104
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:04,300
And a few minutes later,
you walk right back in...

105
00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:08,233
...and you get back to doing it.

106
00:05:11,665 --> 00:05:13,565
(amplified heartbeat)

107
