110
00:05:35,932 --> 00:05:38,832
NARRATOR: Richard Nixon had
taken office as president

111
00:05:38,932 --> 00:05:41,966
in January of 1969,

112
00:05:42,066 --> 00:05:44,300
pledged to restore law and order

113
00:05:44,399 --> 00:05:46,632
and end the war with honor.

114
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,899
(gunfire) Things were calmer at home,

115
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,899
but in Vietnam, peace was no closer.

116
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,565
("Dazed and Confused" continues)

117
00:05:55,665 --> 00:05:59,065
American soldiers still
died pursuing guerrillas

118
00:05:59,165 --> 00:06:02,000
who appeared and disappeared like phantoms.

119
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:06,165
Americans still died capturing hills

120
00:06:06,266 --> 00:06:09,565
only to give them up and have
to take them back again.

121
00:06:09,665 --> 00:06:13,832
Men and materiel were still
flowing into the south

122
00:06:13,932 --> 00:06:17,466
despite the controversial
bombing of Cambodia.

123
00:06:17,565 --> 00:06:21,165
Through it all, Hanoi remained immovable.

124
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:24,199
The communists insisted
there could be no peace

125
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:28,000
until the Saigon government was replaced

126
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:32,500
and the United States
withdrew from Vietnam.

127
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,533
Meanwhile, the American
public was losing patience.

128
00:06:36,632 --> 00:06:38,332
♪

129
00:06:43,766 --> 00:06:45,500
(men shouting)

130
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,500
(gunfire fades)

131
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:52,432
Privately, Nixon knew that
military victory was impossible,

132
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:54,132
that things would have to be settled

133
00:06:54,233 --> 00:06:57,432
at the bargaining table in Paris.

134
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:58,865
He had to find a way

135
00:06:58,966 --> 00:07:01,233
to extricate Americans from Vietnam

136
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:03,399
without seeming to surrender.

137
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:05,365
Nixon also believed

138
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:08,333
his reputation as an
implacable anti-communist

139
00:07:08,432 --> 00:07:11,300
could work to his advantage with Hanoi.

140
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:13,733
"We'll just slip the
word to them," he said,

141
00:07:13,832 --> 00:07:17,699
"you know, 'Nixon's
obsessed about communism.

142
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,065
"'We can't restrain him when he's angry,

143
00:07:20,165 --> 00:07:23,000
"and he has his hand on
the nuclear button, '

144
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,266
"and Ho Chi Minh will
be in Paris in two days

145
00:07:26,365 --> 00:07:29,266
begging for peace."

146
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:33,399
But Ho Chi Minh was old and ailing now.

147
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,566
And Le Duan and the other men

148
00:07:35,665 --> 00:07:38,733
who had been calling the
shots in Hanoi for years

149
00:07:38,832 --> 00:07:41,300
had no intention of giving up their goal

150
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:45,066
of uniting their country
under communist control.

151
00:07:45,165 --> 00:07:47,308
("While My Guitar Gently
Weeps" by the Beatles playing)

152
00:07:47,332 --> 00:07:50,865
Richard Nixon, having promised
a swift end to the war,

153
00:07:50,966 --> 00:07:54,165
would, like all the presidents
who came before him,

154
00:07:54,266 --> 00:07:56,500
end up widening it.

155
00:07:56,600 --> 00:08:00,199
In the process, he would
re-ignite opposition to the war

156
